canonical:
  title: 柳議政 觀 挽章
  author: 尹淮
  language: lzh
  text: 如晦淸風傅說星黃扉白屋短長亭堂堂朝著有元老兖兖相門生列卿國論不須稽卜筮山頹無復見儀形曾叨家叔同年契執紼難禁老淚傾
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 柳議政 觀 挽章
  author: 尹淮
  language: lzh
  text: 如晦淸風傅說星。黃扉白屋短長亭。堂堂朝著有元老。兖兖相門生列卿。國論不須稽卜筮。山頹無復見儀形。曾叨家叔同年契。執紼難禁老淚傾。
korean:
  title: 유의정 관 만장
  author: 윤회
  language: kor
  text: |-
    여회의 청풍 부열(傅說)의 별 타고 나서
    누른 문과 초가집 10리 길 되었네
    조정엔 당당히 원로 한 분 계셨네
    상문에 주렁주렁 공경들이 났도다
    국론을 정할 땐 점괘 필요 없다 하더니
    태산이 무너지고 나자 의용을 다시 볼 길 없네
    더욱 임과 가숙과는 동년의 오랜 친교
    영여를 끌어 잡으니 늙은 눈물 쏟아지네
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0200_010_0550&viewSync=OT
  footnotes:
  - key: '[주-D001] 부열(傅說)의 별 : '
    value: 은(殷)나라 어진 재상 부열(傅說)이 죽어서 하늘에 별이 되었다. 《莊子》
english:
  title: Elegy for Minister Yu of the Willow Gate
  author: Yun Hoe
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Like Hui the wise, with clear winds you rode the star of Puryeol,
    From golden gate to thatched cottage, ten leagues of memory remain.
    In court you stood dignified, an elder of the realm,
    From noble houses sprung forth ministers and lords in succession.

    For settling the nation's will, they said no divination was needed—
    Yet now the mountain has fallen, and your noble form returns no more.
    How deeply we shared those bonds, you and I, same year of our covenant,
    Grasping the funeral rope, these aged eyes overflow with tears.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: 'Puryeol (傅說): A wise minister of the Yin dynasty who became a star after his death, as recorded in the Zhuangzi. Here used to honor the deceased minister.'
  - key: ''
    value: The 'golden gate and thatched cottage' likely refers to the distance between official life and retirement.
  - key: ''
    value: The 'funeral rope' (영여/纓紼) refers to the cord used in funeral rites, with the speaker unable to refrain from weeping while performing these last respects.
